**The scene starts with Jack and Rose standing on the bow of the ship, looking out at the vast expanse of the ocean. The wind is blowing strongly and Rose is shivering from the cold.] Jack: [smiling] "You're shivering." Rose: [nervously] "It's just the cold. I'm fine." Jack: "Here." [He takes off his coat and drapes it over her shoulders.] "Better?" Rose: [grateful] "Thank you." [They continue to look out at the ocean in silence for a moment.] Jack: [breaking the silence] "You know, I never really understood why the ocean was so captivating until I came aboard this ship. It's like staring into infinity." Rose: [smiling] "It's funny, isn't it? All these people, all their worries and their problems...and the ocean just goes on and on, oblivious." Jack: [nodding] "I know what you mean. It's humbling, in a way." [They fall into a comfortable silence again, but Rose suddenly looks uneasy.] Rose: [hesitantly] "Jack...can I ask you something?" Jack: [concerned] "Of course. Anything." Rose: [taking a deep breath] "Do you believe in destiny?" Jack: [surprised] "Destiny? That's a heavy question." Rose: [nodding] "I know. But I can't help thinking...what if we were meant to meet here, on this ship? What if we were meant to be together?" Jack: [smiling softly] "Rose, I don't know about destiny. But I do know that I'm glad I met you. And I'm glad we're here, together, right now." [They share a meaningful look, and Rose leans in to kiss Jack. Suddenly, the ship lurches and they both stumble.] Jack: [urgent] "Come on, we need to get back to the deck." [They start running towards the stairs, but the ship lurches again and they both fall to the ground. Chaos ensues as people start screaming and running in panic.
